0.5670000000000001 w
0 G
BT
/F1 12 Tf
13.7999999999999989 TL
0 g
42.5196850393700814 785.1970866141732586 Td
(Effective API design focuses on clear, intuitive, and consistent resource modeling.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (**Identifying REST Resources:**) Tj
T* (*   Think of nouns, not verbs. Resources represent data entities \(e.g., `users`, `products`,) Tj
T* (`orders`\).) Tj
T* (*   They should be distinct, identifiable, and addressable.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (**URI Design Guidelines:**) Tj
T* (*   **Use nouns:** `GET /users`, `GET /products/123` \(good\); `GET /getAllUsers` \(bad\).) Tj
T* (*   **Use plural nouns for collections:** `/users` rather than `/user` for a collection.) Tj
T* (*   **Keep URIs simple and intuitive:** Easy to guess and understand.) Tj
T* (*   **Use hierarchy for related resources:** `/users/{id}/orders` for orders belonging to a specific) Tj
T* (user.) Tj
T* (*   **Avoid file extensions in URIs:** Use `Accept` header for content type negotiation.) Tj
T* (*   **Use lowercase letters, hyphens for readability:** `/user-accounts` vs `/UserAccounts`.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (**Hierarchical vs. Flat Resource Structures:**) Tj
T* (*   **Hierarchical:** Reflects relationships between resources \(e.g.,) Tj
T* (`/customers/{customerId}/orders/{orderId}`\). Good for naturally nested data.) Tj
T* (*   **Flat:** All resources at the top level \(e.g., `/customers`, `/orders`\). Simpler for unrelated) Tj
T* (resources.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (**Using Nouns vs. Verbs in Endpoints:**) Tj
T* (*   **Nouns:** Used in URIs to identify resources \(e.g., `/products`\).) Tj
T* (*   **Verbs:** Used as HTTP methods to describe the action on the resource \(e.g., `GET`,) Tj
T* (`POST`, `PUT`, `DELETE`\).) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (**Designing CRUD Operations:**) Tj
T* (*   **Create:** `POST /collection` \(e.g., `POST /users` to create a new user\).) Tj
T* (*   **Read \(Collection\):** `GET /collection` \(e.g., `GET /users` to list all users\).) Tj
T* (*   **Read \(Single\):** `GET /collection/{id}` \(e.g., `GET /users/123` to get user with ID 123\).) Tj
T* (*   **Update \(Full\):** `PUT /collection/{id}` \(e.g., `PUT /users/123` to replace user 123) Tj
T* (completely\).) Tj
T* (*   **Update \(Partial\):** `PATCH /collection/{id}` \(e.g., `PATCH /users/123` to update specific) Tj
T* (fields of user 123\).) Tj
T* (*   **Delete:** `DELETE /collection/{id}` \(e.g., `DELETE /users/123`\).) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (**Query Parameters, Filters, Sorting, and Pagination:**) Tj
T* (Used to modify the behavior of a GET request.) Tj
T* (*   **Query Parameters:** General-purpose key-value pairs \(`/products?category=electronics`\).) Tj
T* (*   **Filters:** Narrow down results based on criteria \(`/products?status=available`\).) Tj
T* (*   **Sorting:** Order results \(`/products?sort=price,desc`\).) Tj
T* (*   **Pagination:** Retrieve data in chunks \(`/products?page=2&size=10`\).) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (**Hypermedia \(HATEOAS\) Concept:**) Tj
T* (Resources should include links to related resources or available actions, making the API) Tj
T* (self-discoverable. For example, a user resource might contain links to their orders or a self-link.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (**API Versioning Strategies:**) Tj
T* (Allows for evolving APIs without breaking existing clients.) Tj
T* (*   **URI Versioning:** Include version in the URI \(e.g., `/v1/users`\). Simple, but URIs change.) Tj
T* (*   **Header-based Versioning:** Use a custom HTTP header \(e.g., `X-API-Version: 1`\). URIs) Tj
T* (remain clean, but harder to test in browser.) Tj
T* (*   **Query Parameter Versioning:** Include version as a query parameter \(e.g.,) Tj
T* (`/users?api-version=1`\). Easy to test, but URIs look less clean.) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
