(Good API documentation is crucial for developers consuming your API. Robust testing ensures) Tj
T* (its reliability and correctness.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (**Importance of API Documentation:**) Tj
T* (*   **Developer Experience:** Makes it easy for other developers to understand and use your) Tj
T* (API.) Tj
T* (*   **Maintenance:** Helps maintain consistency and aids in debugging.) Tj
T* (*   **Onboarding:** Speeds up the process of new developers joining a project.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (**OpenAPI Specification Overview:**) Tj
T* (*   A language-agnostic, open standard for describing REST APIs. It defines a standard format to) Tj
T* (describe endpoints, operations, input/output parameters, authentication methods, etc.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (**Using Swagger UI/Swagger Editor:**) Tj
T* (*   **Swagger UI:** A tool that generates interactive API documentation from an OpenAPI) Tj
T* (Specification. Allows users to visualize and interact with the API's resources without any) Tj
T* (implementation logic.) Tj
T* (*   **Swagger Editor:** A browser-based editor to write and validate OpenAPI YAML/JSON) Tj
T* (definitions.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (**Generating OpenAPI Docs Automatically:**) Tj
T* (Many frameworks \(like Spring Boot with Springdoc-OpenAPI\) can automatically generate) Tj
T* (OpenAPI specifications from your code \(e.g., annotations on controllers\), reducing manual effort) Tj
T* (and ensuring documentation stays synchronized with the code.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (**Automated API Testing with Postman, cURL, JUnit/TestNG:**) Tj
T* (*   **Postman:** A popular tool for API development, testing, and documentation. Allows sending) Tj
T* (requests, inspecting responses, and automating test suites.) Tj
T* (*   **cURL:** A command-line tool for transferring data with URLs. Useful for quick manual) Tj
T* (testing and scripting API calls.) Tj
T* (*   **JUnit/TestNG:** Unit testing frameworks for Java. Used for writing automated tests for) Tj
T* (individual API components \(e.g., controller methods, service logic\). Integrates well into CI/CD) Tj
T* (pipelines.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (**Mock Servers & API Simulation:**) Tj
T* (*   **Mock Servers:** Simulate API responses without a live backend. Useful for frontend) Tj
T* (development, testing edge cases, or when the backend is not yet ready. Tools like MockLab,) Tj
T* (WireMock.) Tj
T* (*   **API Simulation:** Allows developers to test how their applications behave when integrating) Tj
T* (with external APIs without actually hitting the external services.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (**Contract Testing Basics:**) Tj
T* (*   Ensures that a service provider \(API\) and a service consumer \(client\) adhere to a shared) Tj
T* (understanding \(contract\) of how the API should behave. It prevents breaking changes and) Tj
T* (ensures compatibility between integrated services. Tools like Pact are used.) Tj
ET
endstream
